The recommended dosing range is 20-60 mg/day, in single doses taken in the evening at bedtime.
The usual recommended starting dose in elderly patients (age â‰¥ 65 years) is 20 mg once a day given in the evening at bedtime. Higher doses should be used only after careful consideration of the potential risks and benefits [see Use in Specific Populations and WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS].
The dose of Altoprev should not exceed 20 mg/day [see WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS].
The dose of Altoprev should not exceed 40 mg/day. [see  WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS and DRUG INTERACTIONS].
In patients with severe renal impairment (creatinine clearance  < 30 mL/min), dosage increases above 20 mg/day should only be considered if the expected benefit exceeds the increased risk of myopathy/rhabdomyolysis. [see  WARNINGS AND PRECAUTIONS and CLINICAL PHARMACOLOGY].
